data.enText: not able to produce children or young animals
completely clean and free from bacteria

data.chText: 无结果的；没有实际价值的

before.enText: of a discussion, an argument, etc.

data.chText: 刻板的；无个性的；缺乏新意的
data.enText: lacking individual personality, imagination or new ideas

data.chText: 那房间让人觉得阴冷而没有生气。
data.enText: The room felt cold and sterile.

data.chText: 他感觉自己既缺乏创造力又没有充沛的感情。
data.enText: He felt creatively and emotionally sterile.
not good enough to produce crops

data.chText: 这种疾病可能导致男女不育。
data.enText: The disease can cause sterility in men and women.

data.chText: 她思量着自己空虚无聊的生活。
data.enText: She contemplated the sterility of her existence.

example: a sterile ideology lacking in originality
unimaginative development of a musical theme

tr: free of or using methods to keep free of pathological microorganisms

value.def: Something that is sterile is completely clean and free from germs.

example.ex: He always made sure that any cuts were protected by sterile dressings...
example.tran: 他总是坚持要用无菌纱布包扎伤口。

value.def: A person or animal that is sterile is unable to have or produce babies.

example.ex: This disease causes sterility in both males and females.
example.tran: 该病会导致男女不孕不育。

value.def: A sterile situation is lacking in energy and new ideas.

example.ex: Too much time has been wasted in sterile debate.
example.tran: 在毫无新意的辩论上已经浪费了太多时间。

example.ex: ...the sterility of Dorothea's life in industry.
example.tran: 多罗西娅在业界毫无生气的生活

trans: 雄性不育系；不育系；雌性植物即雄性不育系
无菌水；無菌水；灭菌水；注射用水
